<raw><![CDATA[ WASHINGTON, Jan 31 (Reuters) - President Barack Obama willdeliver remarks on the U.S. budget on Monday, the White Housesaid on Sunday. He is to speak about the fiscal situation at 10:45 a.m. EST(1545 GMT), shortly after the 10 a.m. release of his spendingblueprint for the 2011 fiscal year that begins Oct. 1 and runsuntil Sept. 30 next year. A congressional source told Reuters that the document willforecast a $1.6 trillion budget deficit for the current 2010fiscal year. The figure highlights a bleak picture in which theshortfall will continue to hover at its highest levels sinceWorld War Two as a share of the economy. (Writing by Caren Bohan; Editing by Eric Walsh)             ]]></raw>
